Problem: Longest Common Prefix
Topic: Strings
Difficulty: Easy

Approach:
Sort the array of strings and compare only the first and last strings. The common prefix between them will be the longest common prefix for all strings.

Time Complexity: O(n log n + m)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    string longestCommonPrefix(vector<string>& strs) {
        if(strs.empty()){  return "";}
        sort(strs.begin(),strs.end());    //sorting both the arrays coz we will check only first and last string 
        string first=strs[0];
        string last=strs[strs.size()-1];
        string result="";
        for(int i=0;i<min(first.size(),last.size());i++){
            if(first[i]==last[i]){
                result+=first[i];
            }
            else{
                break;
            }
        }
        return result;  
    }
};
